29/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The official results of the November 2002 national census will be presented in late November or early December, according to Diaz Munoz, head of Eurostat. He said Tuesday (28 October) that the Macedonian Statistical Bureau and the international monitoring mission are in the final phase of processing results. The population's ethnic composition is a major point of contention among the country's main political parties.
In other news, leaders of the ruling parties met Tuesday evening to discuss the long-rumoured restructuring of the multiethnic cabinet. Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski reportedly will announce the reshuffle next month. (Utrinski Vesnik - 29/10/03; MIA, MTV1, Makfax, A1 TV - 28/10/03)
